"{\"uid\": \"interaksyon.philstar.com-trends-spotlights-2024-04-23-274279-olympics-usada-wants-investigation-into-china-swimming-welcomes-wada-lawsuit\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The head of the United States Anti-Doping Agency demanded on Monday an investigation into the World Anti-Doping Agency's (WADA) handling of 23 positive tests by Chinese swimmers and welcomed the global body's threat of legal action.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16, \"end\": 48, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 16, \"end\": 48, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998858155948301, \"rank\": 9.07296018885344e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The head\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 61, \"to\": 67}, {\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 68, \"to\": 84}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Anti-Doping Agency's (WADA) handling\", \"from\": 90, \"to\": 136}, {\"ngram\": \"23 positive tests\", \"from\": 140, \"to\": 157}, {\"ngram\": \"the global body's threat\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 215}, {\"ngram\": \"legal action\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During a nearly two hour Zoom call with the media WADA fired back at critics and provided detailed explanation of its decision not to pursue sanctions on the swimmers, who tested positive for trimetazidine (TMZ) months before the COVID-delayed Tokyo Olympics began in July 2021.\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 478, \"end\": 492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9365995994724574, \"rank\": 0.06769210713619156, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a nearly two hour\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 258}, {\"ngram\": \"Zoom\", \"from\": 259, \"to\": 263}, {\"ngram\": \"the media WADA\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 288}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 310}, {\"ngram\": \"detailed explanation\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 344}, {\"ngram\": \"its decision\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 360}, {\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 384}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 400}, {\"ngram\": \"trimetazidine\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 439}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 444}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The swimmers escaped punishment after an investigation by Chinese authorities ruled the adverse analytical findings, or AAFs, were the result of being inadvertently exposed to the drug through contamination.\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998858155948301, \"rank\": 9.07296018885344e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The swimmers\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"punishment\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"the adverse analytical findings\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 629}, {\"ngram\": \"AAFs\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 638}, {\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"the drug\", \"from\": 690, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A report determined that all the swimmers that tested positive were staying at the same hotel where traces of heart medication TMZ were found in the kitchen, the extraction unit above the hall and drainage units.\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A report\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 731}, {\"ngram\": \"all the swimmers\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"the same hotel\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 816}, {\"ngram\": \"traces\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"heart medication TMZ\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"the kitchen\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"the hall and drainage units\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was no explanation for how the TMZ found its way into the hotel.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3397460224661424e-18, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no explanation\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"its way\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"the hotel\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China's 30-member swimming team won six medals at the Tokyo Games, including three golds.\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997953505255182, \"rank\": 0.0002040526437182886, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"six medals\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1055}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"three golds\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The whole situation is a tragedy for clean athletes around the world,\\\" USADA chief Travis Tygart told Reuters.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1172, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travis Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\"}, {\"begin\": 1203, \"end\": 1210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3131581825317453e-14, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The whole situation\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1120}, {\"ngram\": \"a tragedy\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1133}, {\"ngram\": \"clean athletes\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1152}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They should have announced the violation they should have disqualified the athletes.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the violation\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1253}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They should have just provisionally suspended (them).\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Clean athletes look at this system and are just frustrated and upset that a number of athletes at this level can test positive for a substance like this and you can have (China) state security create this excuse and then that gets signed off on by the global regulator.\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9997953505255182, \"rank\": 0.0002040526437182886, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Clean athletes\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1370}, {\"ngram\": \"this system\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1438}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1450}, {\"ngram\": \"this level\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1464}, {\"ngram\": \"a substance\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"this excuse\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1567}, {\"ngram\": \"the global regulator\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Athletes are calling for a review and an investigation and we have to get to the bottom of how this possibly happened.\\\"\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1636}, {\"ngram\": \"a review\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1682}, {\"ngram\": \"the bottom\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1715}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The New York Times also reported on Monday that the White House was calling for an inquiry into the Chinese swimmers and would bring it up when anti-doping officials meet in Washington this week.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.280850598272941e-15, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.780875035566028, \"rank\": 0.2806055449283377, \"text\": \"White House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 1849, \"end\": 1856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998858155948301, \"rank\": 9.07296018885344e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Washington\", \"score\": 0.763237597311717, \"rank\": 0.3029445299559977, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Washington\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1791}, {\"ngram\": \"an inquiry\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-doping officials\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 1914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA conceded it conducted no on-the-ground investigation of its own and instead relied on a China doping agency (CHINADA) report then employed their own scientific experts and external legal counsel to test the contamination theory.\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 2179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1950}, {\"ngram\": \"the-ground\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2067}, {\"ngram\": \"their own scientific experts\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2118}, {\"ngram\": \"external legal counsel\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2145}, {\"ngram\": \"the contamination theory\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2178}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With help from leaders of its science and legal affairs departments and investigative unit, WADA presented a detailed step-by-step analysis of how it reached its conclusion but Tygart remained sceptical.\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"help\", \"from\": 2186, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"leaders\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2203}, {\"ngram\": \"its science and legal affairs departments\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2248}, {\"ngram\": \"investigative unit\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2271}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"step\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2311}, {\"ngram\": \"its conclusion\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We really appreciate WADA opening up and providing some information about their process,\\\" said Tygart.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2482, \"end\": 2488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA opening\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2420}, {\"ngram\": \"some information\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2454}, {\"ngram\": \"their process\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was unfortunately very unsatisfying and actually opened up a whole load of questions\\u2026 that need to be answered and actually investigated.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2631, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a whole load\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2565}, {\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2578}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They (WADA) have effectively flipped strict liability on its head.\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2644}, {\"ngram\": \"strict liability\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2687}, {\"ngram\": \"its head\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They have had an authoritarian government with its secret security system provide a defences that they really do not question or challenge.\\\"\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an authoritarian government\", \"from\": 2717, \"to\": 2744}, {\"ngram\": \"its secret security system\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2776}, {\"ngram\": \"a defences\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA and USADA appear on a collision course over the case with Tygart calling ruling a \\\"potential cover-up\\\" and WADA threatening legal action.\", \"from\": 2845, \"to\": 2987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2854, \"end\": 2859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 2908, \"end\": 2914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2845, \"to\": 2849}, {\"ngram\": \"a collision course\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2888}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2902}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"potential cover-up\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 2951}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2957, \"to\": 2961}, {\"ngram\": \"legal action\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 2986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If WADA chooses to go that route, Tygart said bring it on.\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 3047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3023, \"end\": 3029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 2996}, {\"ngram\": \"that route\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3021}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I would welcome it because it would be a lot of fun to see the discovery between the emails and the discussion why they decided not to follow the rules and cover this situation up,\\\" said Tygart.\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3237, \"end\": 3243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3094}, {\"ngram\": \"fun\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3101}, {\"ngram\": \"the discovery\", \"from\": 3109, \"to\": 3122}, {\"ngram\": \"the emails\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3141}, {\"ngram\": \"the discussion\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3160}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3201}, {\"ngram\": \"this situation\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3226}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had a board member one time say if you are not being sued or being threatened to be sued, then you are not doing your job.\", \"from\": 3246, \"to\": 3371, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a board member\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3267}, {\"ngram\": \"one time\", \"from\": 3268, \"to\": 3276}, {\"ngram\": \"your job\", \"from\": 3362, \"to\": 3370}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's part of the job.\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3395, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3383}, {\"ngram\": \"the job\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3394}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Obviously, it does not make anybody happy it's a diversion from the actual facts of the case.\", \"from\": 3397, \"to\": 3491, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anybody\", \"from\": 3426, \"to\": 3433}, {\"ngram\": \"a diversion\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3456}, {\"ngram\": \"the actual facts\", \"from\": 3462, \"to\": 3478}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what WADA should be spending its money on and actually doing a real investigation, not having lawyers review whether they should sue me or media outlets that they are threatening to do.\\\"\", \"from\": 3493, \"to\": 3687, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 3506, \"to\": 3510}, {\"ngram\": \"its money\", \"from\": 3530, \"to\": 3539}, {\"ngram\": \"a real investigation\", \"from\": 3562, \"to\": 3582}, {\"ngram\": \"lawyers\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3602}, {\"ngram\": \"media outlets\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- Reporting by Steve Keating in Toronto, editing by Pritha Sarkar\", \"from\": 3689, \"to\": 3754, \"entities